label.value: Vulvar Cancer cM0 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Vulvar cancer without evidence of distant metastasis (no pathological M0; use clinical M to complete stage group). (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Vulvar Cancer cM1 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Vulvar cancer with distant metastasis (including pelvic lymph node metastasis). (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Vulvar Cancer Pathologic TNM Finding v8

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of vulvar cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system.

label.value: Vulvar Cancer Pathologic Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v8

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of vulvar cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.

label.value: Vulvar Cancer pM1 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Vulvar cancer with distant metastasis (including pelvic lymph node metastasis). (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Vulvar Cancer Pathologic Primary Tumor TNM Finding v8

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of vulvar cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor. The definitions of the T categories correspond to the stages accepted by FIGO. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Vulvar Cancer pTX TNM Finding v8

value.value: Vulvar cancer in which the primary tumor cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Recombinant Neurotrophins
SAM Domain

value.value: The approximately 70 amino acid SAM (Sterile Alpha Motif) domain has been identified in over 400 different proteins with diverse cellular function, from yeast to man. SAM domains have been implicated in mediating protein-protein interaction via the formation of homo and hetero-typic oligomers. The residues at the interface of the EphA4 and EphB2 SAM domain homodimers have been mapped, but the factors that determine specificity remain to be determined. (Pawson Lab, SLRI, Mount Sinai Hospital, 2003)

label.value: Vulvar Cancer pT0 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Vulvar cancer with no evidence of primary tumor. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Vulvar Cancer pT1 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Vulvar cancer with tumor confined to the vulva and/or perineum. Multifocal lesions should be designated as such. The largest lesion or the lesion with the greatest depth of invasion will be the target lesion identified to address the highest pT stage. Depth of invasion is defined as the measurement of the tumor from the epithelial-stromal junction of the adjacent most superficial dermal papilla to the deepest point of invasion. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Vulvar Cancer pT1a TNM Finding v8

value.value: Vulvar cancer with lesion measuring 2 cm or less, confined to the vulva and/or perineum, and with stromal invasion of 1.0 mm or less. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Vulvar Cancer pT1b TNM Finding v8

value.value: Vulvar cancer with lesion measuring more than 2 cm, or any size with stromal invasion of more than 1.0 mm, confined to the vulva and/or perineum. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Vulvar Cancer pT2 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Vulvar cancer with tumor of any size with extension to adjacent perineal structures (lower/distal third of the urethra, lower/distal third of the vagina, anal involvement). (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Vulvar Cancer pT3 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Vulvar cancer with tumor of any size with extension to any of the following: upper/proximal two-thirds of the urethra, upper/proximal two-thirds of the vagina, bladder mucosa, or rectal mucosa; or fixed to pelvic bone. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Vulvar Cancer Pathologic Regional Lymph Nodes TNM Finding v8

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of vulvar cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.

label.value: Vulvar Cancer pNX TNM Finding v8

value.value: Vulvar cancer in which the regional lymph nodes cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Vulvar Cancer pN0 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Vulvar cancer with no regional lymph node metastasis. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Vulvar Cancer pN0(i+) TNM Finding v8

value.value: Vulvar cancer with isolated tumor cells in regional lymph node(s) no greater than 0.2 mm. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)
A chromosome band present on 15q

label.value: Vulvar Cancer pN1 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Vulvar cancer with regional lymph node metastasis with one or two lymph node metastases each less than 5 mm, or one lymph node metastasis equal to 5 mm. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Vulvar Cancer pN1a TNM Finding v8

value.value: Vulvar cancer with regional lymph node metastasis with one or two lymph node metastases each less than 5 mm. It includes micrometastasis, N1mi. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Vulvar Cancer pN1b TNM Finding v8

value.value: Vulvar cancer with one lymph node metastasis equal to 5 mm. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Vulvar Cancer pN2 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Vulvar cancer with regional lymph node metastasis with three or more lymph node metastases each less than 5 mm, or two or more lymph node metastases equal to 5 mm, or lymph node(s) with extranodal extension. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Vulvar Cancer pN2a TNM Finding v8

value.value: Vulvar cancer with three or more lymph node metastases each less than 5 mm. It includes micrometastasis, N2mi. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Vulvar Cancer pN2b TNM Finding v8

value.value: Vulvar cancer with two or more lymph node metastases equal to 5 mm. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Vulvar Cancer pN2c TNM Finding v8

value.value: Vulvar cancer with lymph node(s) metastasis with extranodal extension. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Vulvar Cancer pN3 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Vulvar cancer with fixed or ulcerated regional lymph node metastasis. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Vulvar Cancer by AJCC v8 Stage

value.value: A term that refers to the staging of vulvar cancer according to the American Joint Committee on Cancer, 8th edition. This staging system applies to all carcinomas of the vulva. Melanoma of the vulva is staged according to the classification for melanoma of the skin. (AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Stage I Vulvar Cancer AJCC v8

value.value: Stage I includes: T1, N0, M0. T1: Tumor confined to the vulva and/or perineum. Multifocal lesions should be designated as such. The largest lesion or the lesion with the greatest depth of invasion will be the target lesion identified to address the highest pT stage. Depth of invasion is defined as the measurement of the tumor from the epithelial-stromal junction of the adjacent most superficial dermal papilla to the deepest point of invasion. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th Ed.)
A chromosome band present on 6p

label.value: Stage IA Vulvar Cancer AJCC v8

value.value: Stage IA includes: T1a, N0, M0. T1a: Lesion measuring 2 cm or less, confined to the vulva and/or perineum, and with stromal invasion of 1.0 mm or less. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Stage IB Vulvar Cancer AJCC v8

value.value: Stage IB includes: T1b, N0, M0. T1b: Lesion measuring more than 2 cm, or any size with stromal invasion of more than 1.0 mm, confined to the vulva and/or perineum. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis.  M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Stage II Vulvar Cancer AJCC v8

value.value: Stage II includes: T2, N0, M0. T2: Tumor of any size with extension to adjacent perineal structures (lower/distal third of the urethra, lower/distal third of the vagina, anal involvement). N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Stage III Vulvar Cancer AJCC v8

value.value: Stage III includes: T1-T2, N1-N2c, M0. T1: Tumor confined to the vulva and/or perineum. Multifocal lesions should be designated as such. The largest lesion or the lesion with the greatest depth of invasion will be the target lesion identified to address the highest pT stage. Depth of invasion is defined as the measurement of the tumor from the epithelial-stromal junction of the adjacent most superficial dermal papilla to the deepest point of invasion. T2: Tumor of any size with extension to adjacent perineal structures (lower/distal third of the urethra, lower/distal third of the vagina, anal involvement). N1: Regional lymph node metastasis with one or two lymph node metastases each less than 5 mm, or one lymph node metastasis equal to 5 mm. N2a: Three or more lymph node metastases each less than 5 mm. It includes micrometastasis, N2mi. N2b: Two or more lymph node metastases equal to 5 mm. N2c: Lymph node(s) metastasis with extranodal extension. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Stage IIIA Vulvar Cancer AJCC v8

value.value: Stage IIIA includes: T1-T2, N1, M0. T1: Tumor confined to the vulva and/or perineum. Multifocal lesions should be designated as such. The largest lesion or the lesion with the greatest depth of invasion will be the target lesion identified to address the highest pT stage. Depth of invasion is defined as the measurement of the tumor from the epithelial-stromal junction of the adjacent most superficial dermal papilla to the deepest point of invasion. T2: Tumor of any size with extension to adjacent perineal structures (lower/distal third of the urethra, lower/distal third of the vagina, anal involvement). N1: Regional lymph node metastasis with one or two lymph node metastases each less than 5 mm, or one lymph node metastasis equal to 5 mm. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Stage IIIB Vulvar Cancer AJCC v8

value.value: Stage IIIB includes: T1-T2, N2a, N2b, M0. T1: Tumor confined to the vulva and/or perineum. Multifocal lesions should be designated as such. The largest lesion or the lesion with the greatest depth of invasion will be the target lesion identified to address the highest pT stage. Depth of invasion is defined as the measurement of the tumor from the epithelial-stromal junction of the adjacent most superficial dermal papilla to the deepest point of invasion. T2: Tumor of any size with extension to adjacent perineal structures (lower/distal third of the urethra, lower/distal third of the vagina, anal involvement). N2a: Three or more lymph node metastases each less than 5 mm. It includes micrometastasis, N2mi. N2b: Two or more lymph node metastases equal to 5 mm. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Stage IIIC Vulvar Cancer AJCC v8

value.value: Stage IIIC includes: T1-T2, N2c, M0. T1: Tumor confined to the vulva and/or perineum. Multifocal lesions should be designated as such. The largest lesion or the lesion with the greatest depth of invasion will be the target lesion identified to address the highest pT stage. Depth of invasion is defined as the measurement of the tumor from the epithelial-stromal junction of the adjacent most superficial dermal papilla to the deepest point of invasion. T2: Tumor of any size with extension to adjacent perineal structures (lower/distal third of the urethra, lower/distal third of the vagina, anal involvement). N2c: Lymph node(s) metastasis with extranodal extension. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Stage IV Vulvar Cancer AJCC v8

value.value: Stage IV includes: T1-T3, N3, M0-M1. T1: Tumor confined to the vulva and/or perineum. Multifocal lesions should be designated as such. The largest lesion or the lesion with the greatest depth of invasion will be the target lesion identified to address the highest pT stage. Depth of invasion is defined as the measurement of the tumor from the epithelial-stromal junction of the adjacent most superficial dermal papilla to the deepest point of invasion. T2: Tumor of any size with extension to adjacent perineal structures (lower/distal third of the urethra, lower/distal third of the vagina, anal involvement). T3: Tumor of any size with extension to any of the following: upper/proximal two-thirds of the urethra, upper/proximal two-thirds of the vagina, bladder mucosa, or rectal mucosa; or fixed to pelvic bone. N3: Fixed or ulcerated regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. M1: Distant metastasis (including pelvic lymph node metastasis). (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Stage IVA Vulvar Cancer AJCC v8

value.value: Stage IVA includes: (T1-T2, N3, M0); (T3, Any N, M0). T1: Tumor confined to the vulva and/or perineum. Multifocal lesions should be designated as such. The largest lesion or the lesion with the greatest depth of invasion will be the target lesion identified to address the highest pT stage. Depth of invasion is defined as the measurement of the tumor from the epithelial-stromal junction of the adjacent most superficial dermal papilla to the deepest point of invasion. T2: Tumor of any size with extension to adjacent perineal structures (lower/distal third of the urethra, lower/distal third of the vagina, anal involvement). T3: Tumor of any size with extension to any of the following: upper/proximal two-thirds of the urethra, upper/proximal two-thirds of the vagina, bladder mucosa, or rectal mucosa; or fixed to pelvic bone. N3: Fixed or ulcerated regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)
A chromosome band present on 16p

label.value: Stage IVB Vulvar Cancer AJCC v8

value.value: Stage IVB includes: Any T, Any N, M1. M1: Distant metastasis (including pelvic lymph node metastasis). (from AJCC 8th Ed.)
